-- S.Korea govt, c.bank say concerned over one-sided trading in fx market
-- By Christine Kim
-- Tue Jul 01, 2014 10:00PM EDT
-- None



SEOUL, July 2 (Reuters) - South Korea's government and central bank expressed concerns on Wednesday over one-sided trading in the foreign exchange market after the Korean won <KRW=> firmed through a critical level against the U.S. dollar in early trading.

The won <KRW=KFTC> hit as high as 1,009.3 per dollar by 0148 GMT, the strongest since July 31, 2008.